-- JPMorgan Names Treasury’s Kingsley Mortgage Co-General Counsel
-- B y   R i c k   G r e e n
-- 2013-05-28T19:57:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-28/jpmorgan-names-treasury-s-kingsley-mortgage-co-general-counsel.html
JPMorgan Chase & Co., the biggest
U.S. lender, named former U.S. Treasury Department official
Darius Kingsley as co-general counsel of mortgage banking.  Kingsley was the agency’s chief of the homeownership
preservation office and had been senior counsel for the Office
of Financial Stability, the New York-based lender said today in
a statement. He will share duties with Denise DesRosiers, who
served as deputy general counsel of mortgage banking.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rick Green in  New York  at 
 rgreen18@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter Eichenbaum at 
 peichenbaum@bloomberg.net  